True Blue Crew, Classic Alert,
- I had it spent already!

45:03.295 --> 45:05.586
- I know. Relax, relax. Relax, will ya?
- and Eager Beaver was last.

45:05.669 --> 45:08.669
You know, it's not so terrible.
I told you it was a long shot.

45:08.669 --> 45:10.878
- I never have any luck. Never!
- All right.

45:10.961 --> 45:13.378
I never won a fucking thing
in my entire life! Nothing! Never!

45:13.462 --> 45:16.961
Will you stay calm?
You gotta learn to be a graceful loser.

45:17.044 --> 45:20.170
If it's the money,
I'll lend you the money.

45:20.170 --> 45:22.170
- I can help you.
- No, it's not the money, Lenny.

45:22.170 --> 45:25.462
I don't care about the money.
I just wanted to win so badly.

45:25.544 --> 45:28.669
What do you want to win for?
We're just out here having a good time.

45:28.753 --> 45:30.961
- You gotta--
- 'Cause I wanted to impress you.

45:31.044 --> 45:34.336
Impress me? What? You know,
you're not running in the race.

45:34.462 --> 45:36.627
What-- You don't
have to impress me. I'm--

45:36.753 --> 45:39.253
Yeah, but I wanted to show you
I could pick a winner.

45:39.336 --> 45:42.836
Hey. Listen, my horse
didn't win either, you know.

45:42.919 --> 45:44.836
Come on, you--
you do impress me.

45:44.919 --> 45:48.544
You're attractive, you're--
you're quick, you have a lot of energy.

45:48.627 --> 45:51.044
- You're obviously
a state-of-the-art fellatrix.
- What?

45:51.128 --> 45:53.836
So-- Nothing, nothing.
I'm impressed. Take--

45:53.919 --> 45:55.836
- Lenny, don't say "nothing."
- I'm impressed.

45:55.919 --> 45:58.336
- You think I'm stupid?
- I don't think you're stupid, no.

45:58.336 --> 46:00.836
- No?
- You know, I think you do
a stupid thing with your life.

46:00.836 --> 46:02.836
But I told you that already.

46:02.836 --> 46:05.295
Well, I don't understand
why it matters so much to you.

46:05.295 --> 46:08.502
Hey, come on. We'll stay for one more
race, and this time I'll bet for you.

46:08.627 --> 46:10.711
- Yeah?
- Let me make the bet.
Yeah. N-No. Come on.

46:10.794 --> 46:12.794
- We'll just go to the window
and I'll make one bet.
- All right.

46:12.919 --> 46:15.003
Please don't pick one
that runs second...

46:15.003 --> 46:17.003
- 'cause I want a winner, okay, Len?
- Yeah. Hey.

46:17.086 --> 46:20.502
You know, they give these horses saliva
tests. I can't guarantee anything.

46:24.086 --> 46:26.794
- I gave you your winnings, right?
- Yeah.

46:26.878 --> 46:30.586
That was a great race.
Too bad the horse only paid 40 cents.

46:30.669 --> 46:33.586
Well, he was a heavy favorite, you know,
and I bet him to come in third.

46:33.669 --> 46:36.586
- At least this way you get something.
- Yeah.

46:36.586 --> 46:38.586
So, you wanna come in?

46:38.586 --> 46:41.794
I gotta go home.
I got a wife and kid. You know, I can't.

46:41.878 --> 46:45.878
You know, you only talk about me.
You never talk about yourself.

46:45.961 --> 46:49.378
It's late for me. You know,
I had a great time, but I gotta go.

46:49.462 --> 46:51.669
I feel I owe you a great fuck.

46:51.753 --> 46:55.753
Hey, do me a favor. Go upstairs,
rest your ulcer, stay in tonight.

46:55.878 --> 46:58.462
I can't stay in.
I got six dates.

46:58.544 --> 47:00.544
Six dates.
Slow night for you, right?

47:00.669 --> 47:04.836
I wish I had the penicillin concession
in your apartment. I'd-- I'd be wealthy.

47:04.836 --> 47:07.544
All right.
So, you're gonna call me again?

47:07.669 --> 47:10.253
Am I gonna call you again?
Yeah, I'll call you. Don't worry.

47:10.253 --> 47:12.544
- You promise?
- I will. I'll call you again.

47:12.627 --> 47:14.836
Okay. I had a great time.

47:14.836 --> 47:16.836
- Bye.
- Okay.

47:16.836 --> 47:18.836
Whew.

47:31.045 --> 47:33.337
- Congratulations.
- Thirty-five years.

47:33.420 --> 47:35.337
- I never thought we'd make it.
- You and Amanda...

47:35.420 --> 47:37.337
have a way to go,
but you'll make it.

47:37.420 --> 47:39.502
- You guys look so young, both of you.
- Yeah, you do.

47:39.628 --> 47:41.502
Well, we've kept
each other young.

47:41.628 --> 47:44.211
Your mother could be your sister,
and you could be brother and sister.

47:44.295 --> 47:47.211
- You could be my-- yes.
- I don't know where that
puts me, but anyway--

47:51.086 --> 47:53.586
She looks so beautiful,
doesn't she, Lenny?

47:53.711 --> 47:55.794
- To me, she always looks beautiful.
- Mmm.

47:55.919 --> 47:57.794
-I just always find her great. And you--

47:57.919 --> 48:00.794
When I said sisters before, I mean it.
You guys look so great.

48:00.878 --> 48:03.378
And it's a wonder,
with all the responsibility...

48:03.502 --> 48:05.794
she has opening
her new gallery.

48:05.878 --> 48:08.502
- It's a lot of work.
- What new gallery? A new gallery?

48:08.502 --> 48:11.170
No, I didn't tell you 'cause,
you know, I don't know until
it's a hundred percent definite.

48:11.170 --> 48:13.502
- Well, did I say the wrong thing?
- But it's not.

48:13.586 --> 48:16.170
- No, sure. No, I just--
- It's a hundred percent definite.

48:16.170 --> 48:18.295
You're so insecure.
It's happening.

48:18.295 --> 48:21.794
- Oh, excuse me.

48:21.878 --> 48:24.295
- What is the story on this?
- It looks like I have the backing,

48:24.378 --> 48:26.253
but it's not totally definite.

48:26.378 --> 48:28.253
- That's why I didn't say anything.
- Your mother said it was definite.

48:28.378 --> 48:30.462
Yeah, well. It seems as if
I do have the backing.

48:30.586 --> 48:33.170
And there is this wonderful space
on Vesey Street. You know it?

48:33.253 --> 48:35.462
- Vesey? Yeah, I know it.
- Yeah, down in Soho.

48:35.544 --> 48:38.961
And it looks like, you know,
we think we can get it.

48:39.045 --> 48:41.961
The Dorians are putting in
some money, but I--

48:41.961 --> 48:43.961
- Well, don't look so happy about it.
- I am happy!

48:43.961 --> 48:47.253
I'm very happy for you, but it's
the first I'm hearing of it, you know.

48:47.253 --> 48:49.753
- And for your mother to tell me--
- Yeah, well, look.

48:49.753 --> 48:52.337
I realize that for a time I'm going
to be busier than usual...

48:52.462 --> 48:54.753
and I know that's
a sore point,

48:54.753 --> 48:57.753
but, you know, it'll be only
'til it gets off the ground.

48:57.753 --> 49:00.253
- Hey, I'm happy for you. I re--
- You are?

49:00.253 --> 49:02.544
- Yes. I just would have
liked to have known it.
- Are you sure?

49:02.628 --> 49:05.420
- The Amanda Sloane Gallery.
I think that it's great.
- Yeah, on Vesey Street.

49:05.544 --> 49:08.920
Believe me.
I haven't even told Jerry Bender yet.

49:09.045 --> 49:12.420
"You've got a fine right, you have,
after the way you treated Mother,

49:12.544 --> 49:14.711
"after the way you treated us all!

49:14.836 --> 49:18.128
"A fine right you've got to come back
in here in your best country manner...

49:18.212 --> 49:21.836
"and strike attitudes
and make stands...

49:21.920 --> 49:24.628
"and criticize my fiance
and give orders...

49:24.628 --> 49:26.920
"and mess things up generally
as if you'd done--

49:26.920 --> 49:28.920
"Well, I can't help it.
It's sickening!

49:29.003 --> 49:31.920
As if he'd done nothing at all!"

49:34.920 --> 49:36.920
Well?

49:37.003 --> 49:38.920
What do you think?

49:39.003 --> 49:41.794
- About what?
- About me.

49:41.794 --> 49:45.003
- You think I'm any good?
- Yes, it's fine.

49:45.003 --> 49:47.003
I-- You know, you're asking
the wrong person.

49:47.003 --> 49:49.003
I don't know that much about acting,
to tell you the truth.

49:49.086 --> 49:51.003
Oh, I can tell
you're not too impressed.

49:51.086 --> 49:54.378
No, no, no. I just thought, you know,
it's a very odd part for you to choose.

49:54.378 --> 49:57.378
- Why?
- Well, you know, 'cause
it's The Philadelphia Story.

49:57.378 --> 50:00.462
- But I lived in Philadelphia.
- What has that got to do with it?

50:00.462 --> 50:04.878
- I know the city.
- What? You pick a part like this--

50:04.961 --> 50:08.378
You should get something
closer to yourself.
It wouldn't be such a struggle.

50:08.378 --> 50:10.462
- You know.
- Well, what part should I play?

50:10.586 --> 50:13.045
You know-- I don't know.
Something closer.

50:13.045 --> 50:15.669
Clint Eastwood doesn't play
a meek little hairdresser.

50:15.753 --> 50:18.045
Well, I could play
a hairdresser.

50:18.045 --> 50:20.378
I-I used to--
I used to do it a lot.

50:20.462 --> 50:22.337
I wanted to be one.
I was very good at it.

50:22.462 --> 50:25.045
- So why'd you give it up?
- Well, I don't know.

50:25.045 --> 50:27.045
One thing led to another.

50:27.045 --> 50:29.170
You know, my aunt worked
in a beauty parlor for years.

50:29.170 --> 50:31.753
She loved it.

50:31.836 --> 50:34.753
Wait. You mean
not be an actress?

50:34.836 --> 50:37.628
Well, an actress
is a very tough life, you know.

50:37.628 --> 50:40.420
- But a hairdresser
could always make a buck.
- A buck?

50:40.544 --> 50:43.337
A buck! An honest buck.
No beatings, no AIDS.

50:43.420 --> 50:45.337
You can meet somebody
that you, you know--

50:45.420 --> 50:48.711
You can get a family, have a real life,
someone that cares for you.

50:48.711 --> 50:50.711
Hey!

50:50.711 --> 50:53.337
Now, don't you think that I want
to meet somebody and get married...

50:53.420 --> 50:55.711
and get the hell
out of the rat race?

50:55.711 --> 50:58.836
I would like to move away
and become a mother and just raise kids.

50:58.920 --> 51:00.836
I don't even want
to be a hairdresser.

51:00.920 --> 51:03.295
If Clint Eastwood wants
to be a hairdresser, just let him.

51:03.295 --> 51:07.295
You missed the point. Clint Eastwood
doesn't want to be a hairdresser.

51:07.295 --> 51:09.920
I had a kid, Lenny,

51:09.920 --> 51:12.420
and I gave him up
for adoption.

51:13.920 --> 51:18.420
It's the sorriest thing
I ever did in my entire life.

51:19.795 --> 51:22.878
There's not a day
that doesn't go by that I don't...

51:23.003 --> 51:25.878
wake up thinking
about him.

51:26.003 --> 51:28.295
Now some lucky family
has him.

51:28.378 --> 51:31.795
I just hope to God that they're
taking good care of him.

51:33.295 --> 51:35.961
Why'd you give him up?

51:35.961 --> 51:38.795
I don't know. I was--
I was all confused.

51:38.878 --> 51:42.087
I had no dough. I-I--
I didn't know what to do.

51:42.087 --> 51:44.170
I--

51:44.253 --> 51:46.170
I didn't even know
who the father was.

51:46.253 --> 51:48.961
It could've been any one
of a hundred guys.

51:49.087 --> 51:51.961
Welcome to planet Earth,
thanks to a broken condom.

51:54.379 --> 51:58.253
Gee. That's tough.

52:00.170 --> 52:02.045
Um.

52:03.253 --> 52:05.753
What about your kid?

52:05.836 --> 52:08.961
Max? M-M-Ma-- You know.
Max is the greatest.

52:09.045 --> 52:11.253
- Yeah?
- Well, sure.

52:11.253 --> 52:13.961
Do you have
a picture of him?

52:14.045 --> 52:17.753
- A picture of Max?
- Yeah. I'd like to see him.

52:17.753 --> 52:19.753
Oh.

52:19.753 --> 52:22.253
Uh, yeah, I guess I--

52:29.628 --> 52:32.628
Oh.

52:34.711 --> 52:38.212
He's very sweet. He--

52:38.337 --> 52:40.212
You're very lucky.

52:40.337 --> 52:42.337
With Amanda, it was fate.

52:42.337 --> 52:44.420
With Linda, it's hubris.

52:44.503 --> 52:49.003
His drive to find out, and now,
to change her life, to control her.

52:49.003 --> 52:51.003
-  Yes.
-  Danger.

52:51.087 --> 52:54.503
Wait. Wait,
I see... danger.

52:54.586 --> 52:58.212
Hey, wait a minute. I don't have
any interest in controlling her.

52:58.295 --> 53:00.295
I'm doing this for Max's sake.

53:00.379 --> 53:04.087
When the kid gets older, inevitably
he's gonna trace his mother.

53:04.212 --> 53:06.379
And, you know, I'd be happier...

53:06.503 --> 53:09.795
if she was married and a--
a hairdresser, you know,

53:09.878 --> 53:12.795
rather than the star
of The Enchanted Pussy.

53:12.878 --> 53:16.878
Danger! I see horrible,
horrible danger!

53:16.878 --> 53:20.670
- Terrible danger!
- Hey, I can handle myself emotionally.

53:20.670 --> 53:24.253
Not emotional danger,
physical danger.

53:24.253 --> 53:27.670
I see a bald man.
He has a lead pipe.

53:27.753 --> 53:30.170
He's breaking your kneecaps.

53:36.544 --> 53:39.170
So, so, uh, what did, uh--
How did Jerry Bender take it...

53:39.253 --> 53:41.753
when you said that
the decision was final?

53:41.836 --> 53:43.836
You know what?
He was amazing.

53:43.962 --> 53:47.962
I thought he'd be upset, but no,
he was very excited and very supportive.

53:48.045 --> 53:50.962
No, he's being--
He was absolutely great about it.

53:50.962 --> 53:53.962
Anyway, I-l'm calling to say
I can't make dinner tonight.

53:54.045 --> 53:55.962
Oh, you're kidding.
It's gonna be great.

53:55.962 --> 54:00.128
Everybody in the Madison Square Garden
organization's gonna be there.

54:00.254 --> 54:02.128
Look, there's no way
I can get away.

54:02.254 --> 54:05.254
The architects are here
and the Dorians are in town from Paris.

54:05.337 --> 54:09.212
And, uh, the architects fly back
to Milan tonight. I can't.

54:09.212 --> 54:12.544
All right, well.
I'll tell you what.

54:12.628 --> 54:15.212
What I'll do is, I'll go home
and I'll put Max to sleep.

54:15.212 --> 54:17.337
I'll spend a little time
there and then--

54:17.337 --> 54:19.628
Then-- Oh.

54:19.711 --> 54:22.628
Uh, look, let me--
I'm gonna call you back. I got, uh--

54:22.711 --> 54:25.128
I'm gonna call you back.
Oh, geez.

54:25.128 --> 54:27.128
It's just against our policy--
-  I understand!

54:27.128 --> 54:29.128
- If you wanna wait right here.
- Whatever.

54:29.128 --> 54:31.087
-Lenny, there's someone here to see you.
-Lenny!

54:31.087 --> 54:33.711
-  Uh, yes.
Uh, c-c-come in. Come in.
- Lenny!

54:33.711 --> 54:36.295
- Th-This is Miss Gildersleeve.
She's an acquaintance.
- You know her?

54:36.420 --> 54:38.795
- Gildersleeve?
- Yes, Miss-- Miss Gildersleeve.

54:38.920 --> 54:41.878
We're old-- It's okay. It's okay.
I'll be in here.

54:42.003 --> 54:44.503
- You don't need anything?
- No, no! I'm fine.

54:44.503 --> 54:46.503
- Okay.
- I'm fine.

54:46.503 --> 54:49.087
- What are you doing here?
- Lenny? Lenny, I got to talk to you.

54:49.170 --> 54:51.503
Ricky threatened to-- to--
to hurt me. He--

54:51.586 --> 54:55.170
- Who's Ricky?
- He takes a percentage of my work.

54:55.295 --> 54:58.795
- He's a pimp, right?
- No, he's like
a business representative.

54:58.878 --> 55:01.087
What do you need a business repre--
You-- You--

55:01.087 --> 55:04.379
All you need is a mattress
and a couple of garter belts.
You're not a conglomerate.

55:04.462 --> 55:06.670
Lenny, he said he
was going to cut me up...

55:06.753 --> 55:09.170
because I told him I didn't
want to work anymore.

55:09.254 --> 55:12.878
Well, I think it's a great
idea that you want to phase out.

55:12.962 --> 55:14.962
- He has no qualms about killing me.
- Ohh.

55:15.045 --> 55:17.254
Listen, we'll call the police.
That's not a big deal.

55:17.254 --> 55:19.878
How can I call the police
with my setup?

55:19.962 --> 55:22.670
You know, I told you
a thousand times...

55:22.753 --> 55:24.753
you're in a hazardous business.

55:24.837 --> 55:27.254
So that's what happens.
Now, so-- Don't go outside.

55:27.254 --> 55:30.462
I'm not going outside. I thought,
just maybe, if you could talk to him.

55:30.462 --> 55:32.962
- Me? What, are you nuts?
- Yeah, because--

55:33.045 --> 55:35.753
Because you're smart and bright
and you got a way with words.

55:35.753 --> 55:37.920
I can't talk to him.
I don't even know the guy.

55:38.045 --> 55:40.920
Yeah, well, he knows it was your idea
that I get out of the business.

55:41.045 --> 55:43.128
So he said he's gonna
kill you too.

55:43.254 --> 55:45.837
- He said he was gonna kill me?
- Yeah, 'cause it was your idea.

55:45.920 --> 55:49.920
He's gonna cut up my face
and put a bullet between your eyes.

55:50.045 --> 55:53.545
Really? Did he--
Did he specify the caliber?

55:53.628 --> 55:57.003
Listen, I just thought maybe
you could just reason with him.

55:57.003 --> 56:00.003
No, I can't.
I-- Listen, I never told you this,

56:00.129 --> 56:02.628
but I got a-- a slight
heart murmur...

56:02.711 --> 56:05.003
and right now
