- I don't know.

1:24:41.880 --> 1:24:44.797
I just know that suddenly
I really miss Amanda.

1:24:44.880 --> 1:24:46.797
But wait!
See who approaches!

1:24:46.880 --> 1:24:49.297
There you are!
Where have you been?

1:24:49.381 --> 1:24:51.797
I've been looking for you
all over.

1:24:51.880 --> 1:24:55.588
I was just out drinking
and thinking about everything.

1:24:55.671 --> 1:24:57.588
Oh, Lenny, I'm sorry.

1:24:57.671 --> 1:25:01.588
I, uh-- I was up all night
thinking how much I hurt you...

1:25:01.671 --> 1:25:04.588
and how much
I'd messed us up for good,

1:25:04.671 --> 1:25:07.588
and the thought
of not being with you.

1:25:07.671 --> 1:25:11.047
I love you.
I don't love Jerry at all.

1:25:11.172 --> 1:25:14.546
We have to put things right,
whatever has to be done.

1:25:30.130 --> 1:25:32.755
she drove upstate to Wampsville and
pleaded with Kevin to take her back...

1:25:32.838 --> 1:25:34.546
but to no avail.

1:25:34.630 --> 1:25:38.546
Anyway, on the way home she was
distraught and felt life held no hope...

1:25:38.630 --> 1:25:42.255
when-- talk about
a deus ex machina--

1:26:14.713 --> 1:26:18.713
So we just had a stabilizing problem
and the thing got a little off balance.

1:26:18.713 --> 1:26:22.713
And then the radio went glitchy, so I
just need to get down and use a phone.

1:26:22.713 --> 1:26:25.672
And thank you very much,
by the way, for stopping.

1:26:25.797 --> 1:26:28.672
My name's Don.

1:26:32.089 --> 1:26:34.089
And so Linda married.

1:26:34.089 --> 1:26:38.797
To a wonderful man who was not uptight
and repressed and accepted her...

1:26:38.797 --> 1:26:42.255
and even laughed at wild tales
of her promiscuous background.

1:26:42.255 --> 1:26:44.755
And so our little
Greek drama comes to--

1:26:44.755 --> 1:26:46.755
Wait, wait, wait.
There's more.

1:26:46.755 --> 1:26:49.755
What more, Tiresias,
blind seer of Thebes?

1:26:49.880 --> 1:26:52.256
Tell 'em just to
call me Tiresias, will ya?

1:26:52.381 --> 1:26:54.256
The handicapped
are always cranky.

1:26:54.256 --> 1:26:57.755
On that night,
Lenny Weinrib and Linda did make love,

1:26:57.755 --> 1:27:00.755
Iike he was Zeus and she
was Aphrodite with an aphrodisiac.

1:27:00.755 --> 1:27:02.755
Get to the point!

1:27:02.755 --> 1:27:06.047
- The point is, Linda did,
that night, conceive a child.
- No!

1:27:06.047 --> 1:27:09.464
Yes. She became pregnant
with Lenny's child.

1:27:09.546 --> 1:27:13.964
But not wanting to complicate his life
with Amanda, she never told him.

1:27:14.047 --> 1:27:16.922
Instead she went off
with her new husband,

1:27:17.047 --> 1:27:21.546
who stood behind her loyally as she
gave birth to a beautiful baby girl.

1:27:21.630 --> 1:27:23.546
Lenny never saw Linda again.

1:27:32.630 --> 1:27:36.005
We can look around the whole store
if you'd like.

1:27:38.130 --> 1:27:40.214
- Lenny!
- I don't believe this! Wh--

1:27:40.339 --> 1:27:42.922
-  Hi.
- What are you doing here?

1:27:42.922 --> 1:27:45.422
- I-I--
- I'm stunned! What happened to you?

1:27:45.422 --> 1:27:47.422
I-I'm living in Connecticut.

1:27:47.422 --> 1:27:50.422
I'm married and my husband Don
is a helicopter pilot.

1:27:50.422 --> 1:27:53.922
You're kidding! Where did you go?
I searched every place for you.

1:27:53.922 --> 1:27:57.880
- It's like you vanished
off the face of the earth.
- Well, we had our moment.

1:27:58.005 --> 1:28:01.880
- But I knew you
would be back with Amanda.
- I can't b-- That's super.

1:28:02.005 --> 1:28:05.381
- S-So y-you're married and--
This is yours?
- Yes! Look at her.

1:28:05.505 --> 1:28:08.672
Oh, God, she's adorable.

1:28:08.797 --> 1:28:10.880
- She's adorable. Very, very--

1:28:11.005 --> 1:28:13.880
- And is-- Is that Max?
- This is Max. This is Max.

1:28:13.964 --> 1:28:16.381
- Hello.
- Max, say hello. This is a friend.

1:28:16.464 --> 1:28:18.381
- Hi, I'm Linda.
- How do you do?

1:28:18.464 --> 1:28:21.588
What a handsome boy.
Amanda must be very beautiful.

1:28:21.588 --> 1:28:25.089
And she's-- You've gotta have
a very handsome husband,

1:28:25.089 --> 1:28:27.089
'cause she has a great face.

1:28:27.089 --> 1:28:30.089
I'm stunned.
I don't know what to say. I'm, I'm--

1:28:30.172 --> 1:28:34.047
- Lenny, it's so great to see you.
- You too. You're okay? Everything--

1:28:34.172 --> 1:28:36.547
Yeah. I'm really good.

1:28:36.672 --> 1:28:38.547
Thank you for everything.

1:28:38.672 --> 1:28:40.547
Oh-- I-I--
I'm speechless.

1:28:40.672 --> 1:28:44.047
I-I-- I gotta go.
I'm sorry. I'm gonna be late.

1:28:44.172 --> 1:28:48.339
- It was great to see you.
- It was great to see you. Great.

1:28:48.464 --> 1:28:51.339
- But they have each other's child.

1:28:51.464 --> 1:28:53.339
And they don't know.

1:28:53.464 --> 1:28:56.339
Yes. Yes. Isn't life ironic?

1:28:56.339 --> 1:28:58.339
Life is unbelievable.

1:28:58.339 --> 1:29:02.047
Miraculous. Sad.
Wonderful.

